Package: healthdata
Title: Automatic downloading for various health-related datasets
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: person("Kevin", "Johnson", email = "kej.johnson@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package will automatically find health related datasets on
the Internet and load them into R for you.  All datasets will downloaded into a
folder called "data" in your working directory.  Datasets will not be
downloaded again if they already exist in that folder.  Options are available
for selected variables and subsetting the data before loading.  Functions are
provided for retrieving Census data and common shapefiles.
Depends: R (>= 3.2.1)
License: GPL-2
LazyData: true
